    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-28T13:00:00-05:00" n="710"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.516/340: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 28, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. My telegram No. 22, March 28, 10 a.m. Chamber of Deputies passed bill of
                    sanction for bank purchase contract this morning by unanimous vote. I am
                    reliably informed that text is the same as that passed by Senate yesterday.</p>
                <pb facs="0810" n="717" xml:id="pg_717"/>
                <p>I respectfully request contents of this and No. 22 be communicated to Armour at
                    Princeton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
